{{Starbox short | name = HE 1256-2738 | image = | caption = | epoch = [[J2000]] | constell = [[Hydra (constellation)|Hydra]] | ra = {{RA|+12|59|01.44}}<ref name=simbad>{{cite simbad|title=HE 1256-2738|accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref> | dec = {{DEC|-27|54|18.5}}<ref name=simbad/> | appmag_v = 16.46<ref name=simbad/> | class = sdOB<ref name=simbad/> | dist_ly = 1000 | dist_pc = 310 | names = HE 1256-2738, EC 12563-2738, USNO-B1.0 0620-00338249<ref name=simbad/> | Simbad=HE+1256-2738 }}
'''HE 1256-2738''' is a [[subdwarf]] located approximately 1,000 [[light years]] away in the constellation [[Hydra (constellation)|Hydra]], with a surface temperature of approximately {{convert|38000|C|F|abbr=on}}. Along with stars [[HE 2359-2844]] and [[LS IV-14 116]], HE 1256-2738 forms a new group of star called [[heavy metal subdwarfs]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Astronomers Discover Two Heavy Metal Stars|url=http://www.sci-news.com/astronomy/science-heavy-metal-stars-01283.html|publisher=[[Science News]]|date=August 2, 2013|accessdate=November 5, 2016}}</ref>
